TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hanratty, Maria J.
AU  - Blank, Rebecca M.
T1  - Down and Out in North America: Recent Trends in Poverty Rates in the United States and Canada*
PY  - 1992
Y1  - 1992/02/01
DO  - 10.2307/2118328
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 107
IS  - 1
SP  - 233
EP  - 254
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper examines why Canadian poverty rates fell relative to U. S. poverty rates during the periods 1970–1979 and 1979–1986. During the 1970s the principal reason for declining Canadian poverty rates is higher economic growth. During the 1980s, however, differences in government transfer policy are the main cause of relative poverty change in the two countries. Virtually all of the 3.3 point fall in relative Canadian/U.S. poverty rates from 1979 to 1986 can be attributed to expansions in the Canadian transfer system and simultaneous contractions in U. S. transfers.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2118328
ER  - 



